1.00	Worlds_Of_Tomorrow	Worlds of Tomorrow	Worlds of Tomorrow is an anthology of science fiction stories edited by August Derleth. It was first published by Pellegrini &amp; Cudahy in 1953. Many of the stories had originally appeared in the magazines Worlds Beyond, Fantastic, Fantasy, The Magazine of Science Fiction, Fantasy and Science Fiction, If, Fantastic Adventures, Future, Startling Stories, Astounding Stories, Weird Tales, The Fantasy Fan and Thrilling Wonder Stories. Abridged editions were published by Weidenfeld &amp; Nicolson in 1955, Berkley Books in 1958 and Four Square Books in 1963.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d3/Worlds_of_tomorrow.jpg
